# Next.js 15 App Router Rules

## General Rules
- Always use Next.js 15 App Router conventions
- Use Server Components by default, Client Components only when needed (interactivity, hooks, browser APIs)
- Mark Client Components with `'use client'` directive at the top of the file
- Use `async/await` for Server Components that fetch data
- Prefer Server Components for better performance and SEO

## File Structure
- Pages must be in `app/` directory following App Router structure
- Use `page.tsx` for route pages
- Use `layout.tsx` for shared layouts
- Use `loading.tsx` for loading states
- Use `error.tsx` for error boundaries
- Use `not-found.tsx` for 404 pages
- Use `route.ts` for API routes (if needed)

## Data Fetching
- Use Server Components with `async/await` for initial data fetching
- Use React Query (`@tanstack/react-query`) for client-side data fetching and caching
- Never use `useEffect` for data fetching - use React Query hooks instead
- Prefer Server Components for static data, React Query for dynamic/interactive data

## Routing
- Use `app/router/routes.ts` constants for route paths
- Use Next.js `Link` component for navigation, not anchor tags
- Use `useRouter` from `next/navigation` for programmatic navigation
- Use dynamic routes with `[id]` or `[...slug]` syntax

## Metadata
- Export `metadata` object from page files for SEO
- Use `generateMetadata` function for dynamic metadata
- Include proper title, description, and Open Graph tags

## Performance
- Use `next/image` for images, never `<img>` tags
- Use `next/font` for custom fonts
- Implement proper loading states and error boundaries
- Use Suspense boundaries for better loading UX

## Providers
- All providers must be in `app/providers/` directory
- Wrap app in `app/providers/index.tsx` in root layout
- Keep providers minimal and focused
